            "notes": [
              {
                "reviewStatus": "draft",
                "provenance": {
                  "pageTitle": "Everlasting Ward",
                  "pageId": 987428,
                  "revisionId": 2655110,
                  "section": "Notes",
                  "excerpt": "There is a bug with Elemental Ward that makes this mod mandatory for anyone with a heat Chroma. The bug occurs when allies gain the buff, they leave the radius, then return to the radius during the same casting of Elemental Ward. Even if allies have taken no damage, upon returning they will keep their normal health and have a huge chunk of empty space where Medi-Ray and other healing sources will attempt to heal, which are wasted in the end."
                }
              },
              {
                "reviewStatus": "draft",
                "provenance": {
                  "pageTitle": "Everlasting Ward",
                  "pageId": 987428,
                  "revisionId": 2655110,
                  "section": "Notes",
                  "excerpt": "For example: an ally with 740 health has their health increased to 1000 by a nearby Chroma. They leave, then come back into the radius and now have 740/1000 health, causing Medi-Ray and Curative Undertow to heal the player, wasting the ability or energy respectively."
                }
              },
              {
                "reviewStatus": "draft",
                "provenance": {
                  "pageTitle": "Everlasting Ward",
                  "pageId": 987428,
                  "revisionId": 2655110,
                  "section": "Notes",
                  "excerpt": "This is not related to the nerf to Elemental Ward that used to allow players who entered the radius to become fully healed each time, this bug occurred after this nerf occurred. What is supposed to happen, is the ally will only heal once, but still gain the extra health each time they enter the radius."
                }
              }
            ],
